720485f-a.title: Manhattan: Hudson Street - Hubert Street
720485f-a.text:
153 to 157 Hudson Street, adjoining and north of the N.W. corner of
ubert Street.
About 1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

720484f-c.title: Manhattan: Hudson Street - Hubert Street
720484f-c.text:
Hudson Street, west side, south from Hubert, te and including
Beach Street, as viewed southwesterly across the former depot site
from Varick Street. Indistinctly shown on the left, appears buildings
on the south side of Ericsson Place (Beach Street), west frem Varick
Street (net shown).
December 5, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
A 1imited view; and showing only the west side of Hudson Street,
between Hubert (right) and Beach (left) Streets.
December 5, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

720483f-a.title: Manhattan: Hudson Street - Hubert Street
720483f-a.text:
(1)
149 to 135 Hudson Street, west side, south from Hubert, to Beach
Streets. This block of houses, with the exception of Nos. 137 and
135, the two 6-story buildings (seen on extreme left) were demolished;
on their site now (1937) stands the 14-story Green Industrial Building.
March 7, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
A portion of the same, showing only Nos. 145 to 139.
March 7, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
